  "texts": [
    "Due to their size, these data are increasingly analyzed by multiple people for a long period of time, raising the demand for interoperable and flexible tools that enable simultaneous editing and distributed analysis across multiple user groups.",
    "In our observation, each community differs in the policies implemented that guide proofreading and analysis, raising the need for specific tools to organize a community around these policies.",
    "Here, CAVE's open API enables anyone to create light-weight services that interface with it, lowering the barrier to extend CAVE with analysis and community organization tools (see NeuVue 47 for one such example).",
    "CAVE is generally applicable to any image dataset that requires the correction and annotation of automated segmentation by multiple users in parallel.",
    "Although EM connectomics has led the way in scaling to large volumes of highly resolved imagery, light microscopy methods using expansion of the tissue have emerged."
  ],
